(1) With six years the school begins for children in Germany.
(2) All children go first four years long together on the elementary school.
(3) After separate itself the ways.
(4) A part the pupil and female pupils goes then on the secondary modern school, which ends after the ninth or tenth school year with the certificate of secondary education.
(5) After search itself the most graduate an apprenticeship training position for a practical profession.
(6) Twice the week the trainees must go (apprentice or apprentices) on the professional school.
(7) There they learn before all practical subject for the future profession.
(8) An other part the pupil and female pupils goes from the elementary school on the junior high school.
(9) You ends after the tenth school year with the termination the middle maturation.
(10) After you goes on a technical college or also on a professional school.
(11) As third possibility it are the secondary school, which prepared on an university studies.
(12) The secondary school includes eight classes.
(13) (Before recently is the time on the secondary school from nine on eight years reduced been.)
(14) On the end pupil of the secondary schools make the university-entrance qualification.
(15) Without university-entrance qualification baccalaureate () you can not study.
